\begin{exercise}
Consider the Langevin dynamics splitting parts in the harmonic potential case,
\begin{equation}
\begin{split}
\mathcal{U}_h^A(\bm{q}, \bm{p}) &= (\bm{q} + h\bm{M}^{-1}\bm{p}, \bm{p}),\\
\mathcal{U}_h^B(\bm{q}, \bm{p}) &= (\bm{q}, \bm{p} - h\bm{q}),\\
\mathcal{U}_h^O(\bm{q}, \bm{p}) &= (\bm{q}, e^{-\gamma h}\bm{p} + \sqrt{kT(1 - e^{-2\gamma h})\bm{M}^{1/2}\bm{R}}).
\end{split}
\end{equation}
Show that method $[\![OABA]\!]$ and $[\![BAOAB]\!]$ are conjugates.
\end{exercise}
Without loss of generality, we prove that the algorithm works in one dimension. In the base case $n = 0$,
\begin{align*}
[\![OABA]\!] &= [\![OAB]\!](q + hp/2m, p)\\
&= [\![OA]\!](q + hp/2m, p - h(q + hp/2m))\\
&= [\![O]\!](q + hp/2m + h(p - h(q + hp/2m))/2m, p - h(q + hp/2m))
\end{align*}

